path.aria-label: This phonics board visually represents the 44 sounds in Australian English. English sounds can have various spellings, posing challenges for students learning literacy. The board aims to offer an interactive resource for parents and students to aid in phonics-based literacy learning.

The buttons represent different spellings, grouped by color according to shared pronunciation, or sounds. Hovering over each button reveals the phoneme symbol (the name of the sound), enclosed between //.
